          _F_o_r_c_e_h_i
               Meant to be used with _x_l_r_8_s_e_t(U1), this program makes
               the low memory driver region appear to be full so that
               drivers and filters can be forced into high memory.

          _P_i_p_e_s
               Allows the output of one program or utility to be
               passed as input to another.  For example, the output of
               one program can be displayed through _m_o_r_e(U1), allowing
               you to take advantage of its searching capabilities.

         Note: Additional programs may have been included after this
         page was written.

         Most of the utilities provide help displays, which are
         available by typing the program name, followed by ----????.
         Several of the programs allow you to customize them by
         specifying default parameters in the file DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD.  You
         can even have multiple copies (with different names) of the
         same utility and each copy can have different default
         actions.

         The _l_o_o_k(U1) and _m_a_p_m_e_m(U1) utilities can be trained to
         recognize additional disk formats and memory modules by
         adding entries to easily editable files.


     DDDDooooccccuuuummmmeeeennnnttttaaaattttiiiioooonnnn
          All of the programs on the _U_t_i_l_i_t_i_e_s _D_i_s_k #_1 comes with
          printed documentation.  The documentation uses different
          fonts in a standard way to improve readability.

          When a program name is mentioned, the name is printed in
          _i_t_a_l_i_c font.

          When a program is mentioned on the manual page of a
          different program, a suffix is included to indicate where
          the documentation for the other program can be located. For
          example, on the manual page for _l_o_o_k, a reference to the
          program _m_o_r_e would appear as _m_o_r_e(U1), which is short for
          _U_t_i_l_i_t_i_e_s _D_i_s_k #_1.  The suffix "(L)" indicates that the LDOS
          or TRSDOS operating system manuals should be referenced.  As
          additional Utility Disks become available, this notation
          will make it easier to locate references.

          When a command line option or a command is discussed, the
          command is shown in bold, such as ----eeeexxxxaaaammmmpppplllleeee.








