          Each program has its own manual pages.  If the documentation
          for a given program needs an odd number of pages, the back
          side of the last page is left blank.  This allows you to
          place the pages in a binder in any order you choose,
          although we recommend that they be placed in alphabetical
          order, with the exception of the _i_n_t_r_o(U1) page, which
          should appear first.

          All manual pages are also provided in electronic form on the
          diskette and can be viewed by using the _m_o_r_e(U1) utility.
          These pages contain the same information as the typeset
          manual pages, but are formatted for an 80 column display or
          printer.  The _i_t_a_l_i_c font is represented by underlining that
          many printers can perform.  The _m_o_r_e(U1) utility recognizes
          the underlining and displays underlined text in reverse
          video.  Text that was in a bbbboooolllldddd font in the typeset
          documentation appears as repeated overstrikes of the same
          character in the electronic form.  On most printers, these
          overstrikes will make the text appear darker than normal
          text.  On the display, bold text looks the same as non-bold
          text.


